cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image recognition and generation. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and the comparison with recurrent neural networks (RNN) further supports this. Additionally, the paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a model for generating sketches based on human inputs. The use of variational auto-encoder (VAE) also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with the generation of sketches. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests a connection to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
